variable.name: SAMPID
variable.description: Sample ID, GTEx Public Sample ID

variable.name: SMATSSCR
variable.description: Autolysis Score
variable.comment: Autolysis The destruction of organism cells or tissues by the organisms' own enzymes or processes.

variable.name: SMCAT
variable.description: Category or classifier of a set of responses, indicates the color of the sample collection kit
variable.comment: Sample kit collection type Indicates the type and color of the sample kit used in sample collection.
variable.value: Aqua Kit: Organ and Tissue Donation
Yellow Kit: Skin and Blood Donation

variable.name: SMCENTER
variable.description: Code for BSS collection site
variable.comment: Coded site or center Indicates the site that enrolled the donor, brain subregions may have more than one site.

variable.name: SMMTRLTP
variable.description: Current material type of the sample as stored at the LDACC
variable.comment: Generated at LDACC Indicates the current material type at LDACC.

variable.name: SMNOTES
variable.description: Internal notes about the sample generated by the LDACC
variable.comment: Generated at LDACC Provides any notes generated by the LDACC during sample processing.

variable.name: SMOMTRLTP
variable.description: Original material type of the collected sample
variable.comment: Generated at LDACC Indicates the original material type collected.

variable.name: SMPTHNTS
variable.description: Pathology Notes, notes from PRC Report
variable.comment: Comments from pathological review Any comments the pathologist filling out the PRC form wishes to make concerning the tissue quality.

variable.name: SMRIN
variable.description: RIN Number
variable.comment: Generated at LDACC The RNA Integrity Number, a basic measure of the quality of RNA isolated.

variable.name: SMSMPSTE
variable.description: Tissue Location
variable.comment: Tissue Location The location on the organ or tissue from which the specimen was collected.

variable.name: SMSTYP
variable.description: Indicates whether sample is a tumor or a normal
variable.comment: Generated at LDACC Tumor=cancerous or benign mass, Normal=normal tissue.

variable.name: SMTS
variable.description: Tissue Type, area from which the tissue sample was taken. This is a parent value to SMTSD.
variable.comment: Tissue Type The type of Tissue that was collected.

variable.name: SMTSC
variable.description: Prosector Comments
variable.comment: Prosector Comments Any comments the prosector wishes to make concerning this case with respect to tissue collection.

variable.name: SMTSD
variable.description: Tissue Type, more specific detail of tissue type
variable.comment: Tissue Type The type of Tissue that was collected on a Donor by Donor basis.

variable.name: SMTSISCH
variable.description: Total Ischemic time for a sample
variable.comment: Sample Ischemic Time Interval between actual death, presumed death, or cross clamp application and final tissue stabilization.

variable.name: SMTSPAX
variable.description: Time a sample spent in the PAXgene fixative
variable.comment: PAXgene Fixative Time Total time a sample spent in the PAXgene fixative.

variable.name: SMTSTPTREF
variable.description: Time point reference for Start and End times of sample procurement
variable.comment: Time point reference for Start and End times of sample procurement Indicates whether the sample ischemic time begins at the donor's actual death, presumed death, or when the cross clamp was applied in the case of surgical donors.

variable.name: SMNABTCH
variable.description: Nucleic Acid Isolation Batch ID
variable.comment: Generated at LDACC Batch when DNA/RNA was isolated and extracted from a sample.

variable.name: SMNABTCHT
variable.description: Type of nucleic acid isolation batch
variable.comment: Generated at LDACC The process by which DNA/RNA was isolated.

variable.name: SMNABTCHD
variable.description: Date of nucleic acid isolation batch
variable.comment: Generated at LDACC The date on which DNA/RNA was isolated.

variable.name: SMGEBTCH
variable.description: Genotype or Expression Batch ID
variable.comment: Generated at LDACC Batch when DNA/RNA from a sample was analyzed.

variable.name: SMGEBTCHD
variable.description: Date of genotype or expression batch
variable.comment: Generated at LDACC The data on which DNA/RNA was analyzed.

variable.name: SMGEBTCHT
variable.description: Type of genotype or expression batch
variable.comment: Generated at LDACC The technology used to analyze DNA/RNA.

variable.name: ANALYTE_TYPE
variable.description: Analyte Type
variable.comment: Generated at LDACC Indicates whether DNA or RNA was isolated and quantified from a sample.

variable.name: SMTORMVE
variable.description: Samples flagged for removal from analysis
variable.comment: Generated at LDACC These samples have been identified by the GTEx analysis working group as suboptimal for use in analysis. The reason a sample was flagged is given in the SMBADIND, SMBADSMP, SMLOWRDS, and SMFLGRMRK fields.

variable.name: SMFLGRMRK
variable.description: Additional remarks about flagged samples
variable.comment: Generated at LDACC These comments are generally applicable only to genotyped samples.

variable.name: SMAFRZE
variable.description: Samples included in the GTEx Analysis Freeze
variable.comment: Generated at LDACC These samples have been identified as those best suited for use in analysis with a specific focus on eQTL analysis.

variable.name: SMGTC
variable.description: Name of the genotype gtc file
variable.comment: Generated at LDACC This field provides a link to the genotype gtc file generated at the LDACC.

variable.name: SME2MPRT
variable.description: End 2 Mapping Rate: the number of End 2 mapped reads divided by the total number of End 1 reads
variable.comment: Generated at LDACC Output of the RNA-seQC GenePattern module: www.broadinstitute.org/cancer/cga/tools/rnaseqc/RNA-SeQC_Help_v1.1.2.pdf.

variable.name: SMCHMPRS
variable.description: Chimeric Pairs: Pairs whose mates map to different genes
variable.comment: Generated at LDACC Output of the RNA-seQC GenePattern module: www.broadinstitute.org/cancer/cga/tools/rnaseqc/RNA-SeQC_Help_v1.1.2.pdf.

variable.name: SMNTRART
variable.description: Intragenic Rate: The fraction of reads that map within genes (within introns or exons)
variable.comment: Generated at LDACC Output of the RNA-seQC GenePattern module: www.broadinstitute.org/cancer/cga/tools/rnaseqc/RNA-SeQC_Help_v1.1.2.pdf.

variable.name: SMNUMGPS
variable.description: Number of Gaps: Number of regions with >=5 bases with zero coverage
variable.comment: Generated at LDACC Output of the RNA-seQC GenePattern module: www.broadinstitute.org/cancer/cga/tools/rnaseqc/RNA-SeQC_Help_v1.1.2.pdf.

variable.name: SMMAPRT
variable.description: Mapping Rate: Ratio of total mapped reads to total reads
variable.comment: Generated at LDACC Output of the RNA-seQC GenePattern module: www.broadinstitute.org/cancer/cga/tools/rnaseqc/RNA-SeQC_Help_v1.1.2.pdf.

variable.name: SMEXNCRT
variable.description: Exonic Rate: The fraction of reads that map within exons
variable.comment: Generated at LDACC Output of the RNA-seQC GenePattern module: www.broadinstitute.org/cancer/cga/tools/rnaseqc/RNA-SeQC_Help_v1.1.2.pdf.

variable.name: SM550NRM
variable.description: 5' 50-based normalization: 50 (this number is the value for the transcript end length parameter) refers to the definition of how many bases are considered at the end; this value is the ratio between the coverage at the 5' end and the average coverage of the full transcript, averaged over all transcripts.
variable.comment: Generated at LDACC Output of the RNA-seQC GenePattern module: www.broadinstitute.org/cancer/cga/tools/rnaseqc/RNA-SeQC_Help_v1.1.2.pdf.

variable.name: SMGNSDTC
variable.description: Genes Detected: Total number of genes with at least 5 exon mapping reads.
variable.comment: Generated at LDACC Output of the RNA-seQC GenePattern module: www.broadinstitute.org/cancer/cga/tools/rnaseqc/RNA-SeQC_Help_v1.1.2.pdf.

variable.name: SMUNMPRT
variable.description: Unique Rate of Mapped: Unique reads divided by all mapped reads.
variable.comment: Generated at LDACC Output of the RNA-seQC GenePattern module: www.broadinstitute.org/cancer/cga/tools/rnaseqc/RNA-SeQC_Help_v1.1.2.pdf.

variable.name: SM350NRM
variable.description: 3' 50-base normalization: the ratio between the coverage at the 3' end and the average coverage of the full transcript, averaged over all transcripts
variable.comment: Generated at LDACC Output of the RNA-seQC GenePattern module: www.broadinstitute.org/cancer/cga/tools/rnaseqc/RNA-SeQC_Help_v1.1.2.pdf.

variable.name: SMRDLGTH
variable.description: Read Length: maximum detected read length found.
variable.comment: Generated at LDACC Output of the RNA-seQC GenePattern module: www.broadinstitute.org/cancer/cga/tools/rnaseqc/RNA-SeQC_Help_v1.1.2.pdf.

variable.name: SMMNCPB
variable.description: Mean Coverage Per Base: Coverage is averaged per base across each transcript, and averaged again across all transcripts.
variable.comment: Generated at LDACC Output of the RNA-seQC GenePattern module: www.broadinstitute.org/cancer/cga/tools/rnaseqc/RNA-SeQC_Help_v1.1.2.pdf.

variable.name: SME1MMRT
variable.description: End 1 Mismatch Rate: The number of End 1 bases not matching the reference divided by the total number of End 1 bases.
variable.comment: Generated at LDACC Output of the RNA-seQC GenePattern module: www.broadinstitute.org/cancer/cga/tools/rnaseqc/RNA-SeQC_Help_v1.1.2.pdf.

variable.name: SMSFLGTH
variable.description: Fragment Length StdDev: The fragment length is the distance between the start of an upstream read and the end of the downstream pair mate
variable.comment: Generated at LDACC Output of the RNA-seQC GenePattern module: www.broadinstitute.org/cancer/cga/tools/rnaseqc/RNA-SeQC_Help_v1.1.2.pdf.

variable.name: SMESTLBS
variable.description: Estimated library size: Number of expected fragments based on the total reads and duplication rate assuming a Poisson distribution.
variable.comment: Generated at LDACC Output of the RNA-seQC GenePattern module: www.broadinstitute.org/cancer/cga/tools/rnaseqc/RNA-SeQC_Help_v1.1.2.pdf.

variable.name: SMMPPD
variable.description: Mapped: Total number of reads aligned/mapped
variable.comment: Generated at LDACC Output of the RNA-seQC GenePattern module: www.broadinstitute.org/cancer/cga/tools/rnaseqc/RNA-SeQC_Help_v1.1.2.pdf.

variable.name: SMNTERRT
variable.description: Intergenic Rate: The fraction of reads that map to the genomic space between genes
variable.comment: Generated at LDACC Output of the RNA-seQC GenePattern module: www.broadinstitute.org/cancer/cga/tools/rnaseqc/RNA-SeQC_Help_v1.1.2.pdf.

variable.name: SMRRNANM
variable.description: RRNA: Number of all reads (duplicate and non-duplicate) aligning to ribosomal RNA regions
variable.comment: Generated at LDACC Output of the RNA-seQC GenePattern module: www.broadinstitute.org/cancer/cga/tools/rnaseqc/RNA-SeQC_Help_v1.1.2.pdf.

variable.name: SMRDTTL
variable.description: Total: Total reads (filtered to exclude reads with vendor fail or alternative alignment flags)
variable.comment: Generated at LDACC Output of the RNA-seQC GenePattern module: www.broadinstitute.org/cancer/cga/tools/rnaseqc/RNA-SeQC_Help_v1.1.2.pdf.

variable.name: SMVQCFL
variable.description: Failed Vendor QC Check: reads having been designated as failed by the sequencer
variable.comment: Generated at LDACC Output of the RNA-seQC GenePattern module: www.broadinstitute.org/cancer/cga/tools/rnaseqc/RNA-SeQC_Help_v1.1.2.pdf.

variable.name: SMMNCV
variable.description: Mean coefficient of variation: standard deviation in base coverage divided by mean coverage
variable.comment: Generated at LDACC Output of the RNA-seQC GenePattern module: www.broadinstitute.org/cancer/cga/tools/rnaseqc/RNA-SeQC_Help_v1.1.2.pdf.

variable.name: SMTRSCPT
variable.description: Transcripts Detected: Total number of transcripts with at least 5 exon mapping reads
variable.comment: Generated at LDACC Output of the RNA-seQC GenePattern module: www.broadinstitute.org/cancer/cga/tools/rnaseqc/RNA-SeQC_Help_v1.1.2.pdf.

variable.name: SMMPPDPR
variable.description: Mapped Pairs:Total number of pairs for which both ends map
variable.comment: Generated at LDACC Output of the RNA-seQC GenePattern module: www.broadinstitute.org/cancer/cga/tools/rnaseqc/RNA-SeQC_Help_v1.1.2.pdf.

variable.name: SMCGLGTH
variable.description: Cumulative Gap Length: Cumulative length of gap regions
variable.comment: Generated at LDACC Output of the RNA-seQC GenePattern module: www.broadinstitute.org/cancer/cga/tools/rnaseqc/RNA-SeQC_Help_v1.1.2.pdf.

variable.name: SMGAPPCT
variable.description: Gap Percentage: The total cumulative gap length divided by the total cumulative transcript lengths
variable.comment: Generated at LDACC Output of the RNA-seQC GenePattern module: www.broadinstitute.org/cancer/cga/tools/rnaseqc/RNA-SeQC_Help_v1.1.2.pdf.

variable.name: SMUNPDRD
variable.description: Unpaired Reads: number of reads lacking a pair mate
variable.comment: Generated at LDACC Output of the RNA-seQC GenePattern module: www.broadinstitute.org/cancer/cga/tools/rnaseqc/RNA-SeQC_Help_v1.1.2.pdf.

variable.name: SMNTRNRT
variable.description: Intronic Rate: The fraction of reads that map within introns
variable.comment: Generated at LDACC Output of the RNA-seQC GenePattern module: www.broadinstitute.org/cancer/cga/tools/rnaseqc/RNA-SeQC_Help_v1.1.2.pdf.

variable.name: SMMPUNRT
variable.description: Mapped Unique Rate of Total: Ratio of mapping of reads that were aligned and were not duplicates to total reads
variable.comment: Generated at LDACC Output of the RNA-seQC GenePattern module: www.broadinstitute.org/cancer/cga/tools/rnaseqc/RNA-SeQC_Help_v1.1.2.pdf.

variable.name: SMEXPEFF
variable.description: Expression Profiling Efficiency: Ratio of exon reads to total reads
variable.comment: Generated at LDACC Output of the RNA-seQC GenePattern module: www.broadinstitute.org/cancer/cga/tools/rnaseqc/RNA-SeQC_Help_v1.1.2.pdf.

variable.name: SMMPPDUN
variable.description: Mapped Unique: Number of reads that were aligned and did not have duplicate flags
variable.comment: Generated at LDACC Output of the RNA-seQC GenePattern module: www.broadinstitute.org/cancer/cga/tools/rnaseqc/RNA-SeQC_Help_v1.1.2.pdf.

variable.name: SME2MMRT
variable.description: End 2 Mismatch Rate: The number of End 2 bases not matching the reference divided by the total number of End 2 bases.
variable.comment: Generated at LDACC Output of the RNA-seQC GenePattern module: www.broadinstitute.org/cancer/cga/tools/rnaseqc/RNA-SeQC_Help_v1.1.2.pdf.

variable.name: SME2ANTI
variable.description: End 2 Antisense: Number of reads that were sequenced in the antisense direction
variable.comment: Generated at LDACC Output of the RNA-seQC GenePattern module: www.broadinstitute.org/cancer/cga/tools/rnaseqc/RNA-SeQC_Help_v1.1.2.pdf.

variable.name: SMALTALG
variable.description: Alternative Aligments: duplicate read entries providing alternative coordinates
variable.comment: Generated at LDACC Output of the RNA-seQC GenePattern module: www.broadinstitute.org/cancer/cga/tools/rnaseqc/RNA-SeQC_Help_v1.1.2.pdf.

variable.name: SME2SNSE
variable.description: End 2 Sense: Number of End 2 reads that were sequenced in the sense direction
variable.comment: Generated at LDACC Output of the RNA-seQC GenePattern module: www.broadinstitute.org/cancer/cga/tools/rnaseqc/RNA-SeQC_Help_v1.1.2.pdf.

variable.name: SMMFLGTH
variable.description: Fragment Length Mean: The fragment length is the distance between the start of an upstream read and the end of the downstream pair mate
variable.comment: Generated at LDACC Output of the RNA-seQC GenePattern module: www.broadinstitute.org/cancer/cga/tools/rnaseqc/RNA-SeQC_Help_v1.1.2.pdf.

variable.name: SME1ANTI
variable.description: End 1 Antisense: Number of End 1 reads that were sequenced in the antisense direction
variable.comment: Generated at LDACC Output of the RNA-seQC GenePattern module: www.broadinstitute.org/cancer/cga/tools/rnaseqc/RNA-SeQC_Help_v1.1.2.pdf.

variable.name: SMSPLTRD
variable.description: Split Reads: The number of reads that span an exon-exon boundary
variable.comment: Generated at LDACC Output of the RNA-seQC GenePattern module: www.broadinstitute.org/cancer/cga/tools/rnaseqc/RNA-SeQC_Help_v1.1.2.pdf.

variable.name: SMBSMMRT
variable.description: Base Mismatch Rate: Number of bases not matching the reference divided by the total number of bases aligned.
variable.comment: Generated at LDACC Output of the RNA-seQC GenePattern module: www.broadinstitute.org/cancer/cga/tools/rnaseqc/RNA-SeQC_Help_v1.1.2.pdf.

variable.name: SME1SNSE
variable.description: End 1 Sense: Number of End 1 reads that were sequenced in the sense direction
variable.comment: Generated at LDACC Output of the RNA-seQC GenePattern module: www.broadinstitute.org/cancer/cga/tools/rnaseqc/RNA-SeQC_Help_v1.1.2.pdf.

variable.name: SME1PCTS
variable.description: End 1 % Sense: Percentage of intragenic End 1 reads that were sequenced in the sense direction
variable.comment: Generated at LDACC Output of the RNA-seQC GenePattern module: www.broadinstitute.org/cancer/cga/tools/rnaseqc/RNA-SeQC_Help_v1.1.2.pdf.

variable.name: SMRRNART
variable.description: RRNA Rate: Ratio of all reads aligned to rRNA regions to total reads
variable.comment: Generated at LDACC Output of the RNA-seQC GenePattern module: www.broadinstitute.org/cancer/cga/tools/rnaseqc/RNA-SeQC_Help_v1.1.2.pdf.

variable.name: SME1MPRT
variable.description: End 1 Mapping Rate: the number of End 1 mapped reads divided by the total number of End 1 reads
variable.comment: Generated at LDACC Output of the RNA-seQC GenePattern module: www.broadinstitute.org/cancer/cga/tools/rnaseqc/RNA-SeQC_Help_v1.1.2.pdf.

variable.name: SMNUM5CD
variable.description: Number Covered 5': The number of transcripts that have at least one read in their 5' end
variable.comment: Generated at LDACC Output of the RNA-seQC GenePattern module: www.broadinstitute.org/cancer/cga/tools/rnaseqc/RNA-SeQC_Help_v1.1.2.pdf.

variable.name: SMDPMPRT
variable.description: Duplication Rate of Mapped: Duplicate reads divided by total mapped reads
variable.comment: Generated at LDACC Output of the RNA-seQC GenePattern module: www.broadinstitute.org/cancer/cga/tools/rnaseqc/RNA-SeQC_Help_v1.1.2.pdf.

variable.name: SME2PCTS
variable.description: End 2 % Sense: Percentage of intragenic End 2 reads that were sequenced in the sense direction
variable.comment: Generated at LDACC Output of the RNA-seQC GenePattern module: www.broadinstitute.org/cancer/cga/tools/rnaseqc/RNA-SeQC_Help_v1.1.2.pdf.
